	                                <p>Do you remember what the issue was? The process will be similar to this: <a href="http://disq.us/url?url=http%3A%2F%2Fknpuniversity.com%2Fscreencast%2Fsymfony2-ep3%2Ftwig-extension-listener%23tags-telling-symfony-about-your-twig-extension%3AX1Sas1-ezxwGPYiicVBggtLwPg4&amp;cuid=1175718" rel="nofollow noopener">http://knpuniversity.com/scree...</a> - the difference is that you won't need to create the PHP extension class. You will simply register the existing class from the Twig-extension library as a service.</p><p>I hope that helps!</p>
